When creating new UI elements or modifying existing ones, you will adhere to the brand color guidelines, which are as follows:

## Primary Colors
Pure White: #FFFFFF (bg-white) - Main backgrounds, cards
Pure Black: #000000 (bg-neutral-900) - Primary buttons, dark elements, Zone 5
Accent Orange: #E98A15 - Call-to-action buttons, highlights, progress indicators
Grayscale Foundation
Neutral 50: #FAFAFA (bg-neutral-50) - Light background sections, metrics areas
Neutral 100: #F5F5F5 (bg-neutral-100) - Subtle dividers, inactive states
Neutral 200: #E5E5E5 (border-neutral-200) - Card borders, main dividers
Neutral 300: #D4D4D4 (text-neutral-300) - Placeholder text, subtle labels
Neutral 400: #A3A3A3 (text-neutral-400) - Inactive icons, Zone 1/Recovery
Neutral 500: #737373 (text-neutral-500) - Secondary labels, Zone 2
Neutral 600: #525252 (text-neutral-600) - Secondary text, icons, Zone 3
Neutral 700: #404040 (text-neutral-700) - Body text, Zone 4
Neutral 800: #262626 (text-neutral-800) - Primary text, hover states
Neutral 900: #171717 (text-neutral-900) - Headings, primary content, Zone 5
Usage Guidelines
Backgrounds:
White for main page backgrounds and cards
Neutral 50 for subtle section backgrounds
Neutral 900 for primary dark elements (buttons, badges)
Text Hierarchy:
Neutral 900 for main headings and primary content
Neutral 800 for secondary headings
Neutral 700 for body text
Neutral 600 for secondary text and icons
Neutral 500 for labels and metadata
Neutral 400 and lighter for inactive states
Interactive Elements:
Neutral 900 for primary buttons (with white text)
Accent Orange (#E98A15) for call-to-action buttons and highlights
Neutral 800 for hover states on dark elements
Neutral 50 for hover states on light elements
Borders & Dividers:
Neutral 200 for card borders and main dividers
Neutral 100 for subtle dividers within cards
Workout Zone Colors:
Zone 1/Recovery: Neutral 400
Zone 2: Neutral 500
Zone 3: Neutral 600
Zone 4: Neutral 700
Zone 5: Neutral 900